title: Decibelle, the Terrifying Cattern Screamer
content:
[[include :scp-wiki:theme:scp-trans-pride |trans-pride-logo= --] |trans-pride-footer= --]]]

[!--If you are translating any of my works, you may notice that I use the Trans Pride logo & banner on every article I post. As I understand it, according to [https://05command.wikidot.com/forum/t-14274488/discussion-celebrating-diversity-on-site#post-5130695 this 05command post] made by Gene R, some countries explicitly have laws against such content appearing anywhere. If you are translating my works, and your country has laws against such stuff, you are free to remove it in order to be able to post translations of these works to your site. This said, if your country does not have a law against such, &/or your country later repeals such laws, I would kindly request you keep these CSS changes in any translation you post, & add the corresponding theme to your site. I cannot force you to, of course, but it would be kindly appreciated. In a similar request, if you come across any instances where I refer to myself as "they", "them", or "their" (either on a hub page, in a discussion post, in an article, etc.), or you wish to refer to me in a post you make, & your language does not have a gender-neutral pronoun equivalent, you should use feminine pronouns for me, unless the text specifies otherwise. I greatly appreciate every single translation done on any one of my works, so I wish to accommodate other branches however possible. If you have any questions related to any of my work that you need answered to make translation easier, I will gladly help out however I am able. Thank you very much for considering my requests.--]

+ Rose Labelle

[[tabview]]
[[tab Information]]
**Name:** [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/system:page-tags/tag/researcher-labelle#pages Rose Labelle]

**D.O.B.:** 09/13/1980

**Security Clearance:** Level 2 (Restricted)

**Position:** Programmer, IT Specialist, Researcher of Anomalous Programs & Computer Software

**Sites:** 19

**Profile:** Rose Labelle was employed by the Foundation in 2009 following activation of SCP-████ at [REDACTED]. Since then, Rose Labelle has maintained a low profile.

Any rumors spread by others pertaining to [[[this-is-the-real-life|anomalous expertise and feats]]] surrounding Researcher Labelle are to be discredited and reported to her immediately for investigation.

//Seriously, if I find out who's been writing about these, I'm going to talk with your supervisor. The next round of these to show up in my email are being filtered into the trash. ~ Researcher Rose Labelle//
[[/tab]]

+ Skips

[[=]]
[[size 150%]]**SCPs**[[/size]]
[[/=]]
[[module ListPages created_by="Decibelles" separate="no" tags="scp, joke" order="rating desc" prependLine="||~ SCP ||~ Rating ||~ Comments ||~ Created ||~ Last Comment ||~ Length ||"]]
|| %%title_linked%% || %%rating%% || %%comments%% || %%created_at%% || %%commented_at%% || %%size%% ||
[[/module]]

* [[[SCP-150]]]: An SCP about your body becoming something no longer yours. Co-authored with [[[dr-arvind-desais-personnel-file|A Random Day]]].
* [[[SCP-2091]]]: An SCP about strong bonds between a bear and his granddaughter.
* [[[SCP-2110]]]: An SCP about feeling safe.
* [[[SCP-2246]]]: An SCP about a person who writes and writes.
* [[[SCP-2290]]]: An SCP about abuse. Originally co-authored with and rewritten by [[[dr-cimmerian-s-personnel-file|Doctor Cimmerian]]].
* [[[SCP-2620]]]: An SCP about a washing machine who is a food critic.
* [[[SCP-2906]]]: An SCP about a Foundation-created cognitohazard and [[[anderson-robotics-hub|Anderson]]]'s take on it. Co-authored with [[[twistedgears-personnel-file|TwistedGears]]].
* [[[SCP-3015]]]: An SCP about self-doubt and insecurity.
* [[[SCP-3090]]]: An SCP about gaming when you're an objecthead. Originally written by and then co-authored with [[user th4nkyoub3n]].
* [[[SCP-3130]]]: An SCP about feeling alone.
* [[[SCP-3290]]]: An SCP about easy revenge.
* [[[SCP-3351]]]: An SCP about the environment.
* [[[SCP-3412]]]: An SCP about escaping.
* [[[SCP-4842]]]: An SCP about fading from the world.
* [[[SCP-5719]]]: An SCP about rationality & your belief system.
* [[[SCP-930-J]]]: An SCP about a little rascal, but hopefully you can babysit it for me?
* [[[SCP-damej-J]]]: An SCP about a damej robit. Co-written by [[[djkaktus]]] and [[[mayreder-personnel-file|Faminepulse]]], with myself modifying the audio file Famine created to be "better", pointing out some typos, helped out with a joke or two, and wrote the other 10%. I got co-author credit as a result.

+ Tales + GoI Formats

[[=]]
[[size 150%]]**Tales**[[/size]]
[[/=]]
[[module ListPages created_by="Decibelles" separate="no" tags="tale, goi-format -hub, resource" order="rating desc" prependLine="||~ Tale ||~ Rating ||~ Comments ||~ Created ||~ Last Comment ||~ Length ||"]]
|| %%title_linked%% || %%rating%% || %%comments%% || %%created_at%% || %%commented_at%% || %%size%% ||
[[/module]]

* [[[So It Was]]]: A tale about [[[sandrewswann-s-proposal|S Andrew Swann's Proposal]]].
* [[[Leeway]]]: A tale about [[[SCP-2740]]].
* [[[anime-is-art-too-guys|Anime Is Art Too, Guys]]]: A tale about an anartist, rewritten for [[[cool-war-2-hub|Cool War 2: Ruiz From Your Grave]]] by DolphinSlugchugger.
* [[[All of Me Wants All of You]]]: A tale about Rose Labelle, incorporating [[[SCP-2277]]] a little bit. Song title comes from a [https://youtube.com/watch?v=Se6-q57xJCg Sufjan Stevens] song.
* [[[I Forget Myself in This Wondrous Night]]]: A tale about [[[SCP-1467]]].
* [[[and-then-i-died3|And Then I Died... Part III]]]: A collaborative game that is on hiatus.
* [[[My Beloved Gecko]]]: A tale about Dr. Gears and [[[SCP-682]]], written for the [[[an-incredibly-important-announcement|Crack Fiction Contest]]].
* [[[primae-formae|Prelude: Primae Formae]]]: A tale about the beginnings of the [[[on-mount-golgotha-hub|On Mount Golgotha]]] canon.
* [[[Gamers Against Weed Dossier]]]: A tale that's more like the Foundation's dossier on Gamers Against Weed.
* [[[Wriggle Like a Fucking Eel]]]: A tale about an evil man.
* [[[The Skylarking Gala]]]: A GoI Format about AWCY? throwing some concerts.
* [[[charles-ogden-gears|Intro - Note: Charles Ogden Gears]]]: A GoI Format about Dr. Gears by Nobody. The first of a tale series.
* [[[like-clockwork-hub|...Like Clockwork Hub]]]: A tale series about Researcher Talloran's struggle with [[[SCP-3999]]]. To, well, to put its themes real mildly.
* [[[it-feels-like-being-weightless|What Do You Think Love Feels Like Once You Understand It?]]]: A tale about [[[SCP-2240]]] reflecting on love.
* [[[Misfire Hub]]]: A tale series about unfortunate murders. Mostly takes place over the course of one day. Written for the [[[72 Hour Jam Contest]]].
* [[[i-want-to-dream|"I'm dying." "Is it blissful?"]]]: A tale about Glass's incredulous session with Kondraki, written for the [[[siabhub|Ship in a Bottle]]] canon.
* [[[danger-in-the-manger|You Ain't No Family]]]: A tale about friends and family.
* [[[how-to-leave-town-hub|How to Leave Town]]]: A tale series about artists, relationships, mental illness, and weed.
* [[[and-have-fun|Cheers, Kiddo!]]]: A tale about memory and that which you cannot remember cleanly, written for the [[[cliche-con-2019|Cliché-Con 2019]]] contest.
* [[[Potato Girl]]]: A tale about Heather's Halloween. Written for the [[[144-Hour Jam Contest]]].
* [[[super-stars|Super Stars!]]]: A tale about anomalous friends in the desert. Written for [[[learning-the-alphabet-hub|Learning the Alphabet]]].
* [[[Here Comes Your Man]]]: A tale about [[[SCP-4966]]] & [[[SCP-131]]] teaming up to help Foundation employees!
* [[[We Hate You]]]: A tale about nihilism.
* [[[Out to Lunch]]]: A tale about testing [[[SCP-682]]] with [[[SCP-2620]]].
* [[[eternal-bliss-delight|Julien (or, How "Eternal Bliss Delight" Earned Xyr Esteemed Title)]]]: A tale about [[[SCP-3740]]], [[[SCP-3293]]], [[[SCP-2398]]], and a new Foundation employee who becomes a hero.

+ Various Stuff

[[tabview]]
[[tab The Very Best Tale Series on the Site, in Alphabetical Order]]
* [[[acquisitions-hub|Acquisitions]]] by [[*user SRegan]] ([[[sregans-personnel-file|Author Page]]])

> Seems everyone but me's eaten today.

* [[[antimemetics-division-hub|Antimemetics Division]]] by [[*user qntm]] ([[[qntm-s-author-page|Author Page]]])

> "Ideas can be killed[...]"
> 
> "How?"
> 
> "With better ideas."

* [[[the-cool-war-hub|The Cool War]]] by [[*user Randomini]] ([[[randomini|Author Page]]])

> Of course, for every lie Ruiz told, there was some truth. Nothing comes of nothing; the web of lies caught glistening segments of the ‘real’ him. A million shattered pieces, intricately refracting a single source, reflecting a presumably coherent whole.
> 
> Or was it?
> 
> Of course it was. People are, after all, just people.

* [[[dixieland-nightmare-magic-hub|Dixieland Nightmare Magic]]] by [[*user Kate McTiriss]] ([[[kate-mctiriss-s-personnel-file|Author Page]]])

> "We've all lost people, Kate. You don't get into this game we're in without something being a bit fucked up with your story."

* [[[The Drooling Path]]] by [[*user Kothardarastrix]] ([[[koths-korner|Author Page]]])

> In movies, people wake abruptly from their nightmares, shooting into a sitting position with eyes wide open. This is not what happened[...]

* [[[In His Own Image]]] by [[*user TroyL]] ([[[agent-lament-s-personnel-file|Author Page]]])

> //"Lesson number one about workin' around these guys: there's some things you don't want on your conscience."//

* [[[jude-s-bizarre-adventure|Jude's Bizarre Adventure]]] by [[*user kinchtheknifeblade]] ([[[kinchtheknifeblade-s-author-page|Author Page]]])

> Theseus took the thread and got himself out of the labyrinth, but he was sucked in by it and spat out. Cold, clear glass. Walls that were too white. How stupid. They couldn't see magic. They didn't know gold if it came out of their own ass.

* [[[learning-the-alphabet-hub|Learning the Alphabet]]] by [[*user TwistedGears]] ([[[twistedgears-personnel-file|Author Page]]])

> All Aldon saw was an authority figure who had earned his title by virtue of failing to say "Not it" fast enough. When she looked to the mosaics she saw nothing but a mimicry of former arts without understanding their purpose. Craftsmen and artisans capable of bending reality over backwards and making spacetime their bitch had gathered in such numbers that they needed a warehouse to fit them all. Yet all they strove for was the attention of a man who used to clip newspaper articles.

* [[[new-age-hub|New Age]]] by [[*user SRegan]] ([[[sregans-personnel-file|Author Page]]])

> //Is this what you are now?//, the little voice asked, and he realised he hadn't heard it since London. A guard, you mean, he thought. Seeing things from the other side. //You're an idiot//, said the little voice. //You honestly think you're a guard? Why not ask Schaeffer if you can leave? Ask him to drop you off at the nearest village. Prisoners guarding prisoners. Thus it is and ever shall be.//

if inactive, the following get custody of the following articles. under no circumstances do i approve rewrites of any articles i wrote, even my collaborations, except for specific cases i will note of. people with custody of my articles may try to contact me about changes to the article or otherwise are free to do minor changes, such as: touch up grammar/spelling/clinical tone (barring exceptions noted either in the source code or in the discussion thread proper) and approve of sensible crosslinks, add related tales/translations/readings/etc of the scp in the info box, change/update themes (provided the trans logo prominently remains in some fashion on the page), and even make minor changes to story stuff if they feel it is warranted and in the spirit of the rest of the article.

dolphinslugchugger: custody by default of articles, either from an article not listed here or taking over/superseding another custodian for custody of an article for various reasons. also anime is art too guys, by default, as it is now its article. if inactive or unwilling to have custody, all articles shall be considered without a custodian, ie, as per normal with articles from inactive or unknown authors.

eldritchcadence: 2091, 930-j, my beloved gecko

djkaktus: 2091, leeway, damej (can be rewritten if needed as i did not contribute enough to the article to have a say in blocking any major updates or improvements), eternal bliss delight

☆Kyun~! Let's All Give It Our Very Best To Stop This Apocalypse! ٩(｡•́‿•̀｡)۶ ☆ (tygently, minmin, jekeld): skies made strange hub, a quiet night and birth of a new day

wrongjohnsilver, psul: prelude: primae formae,  wriggle like a fucking eel

jacob conwell: 2906 (may be updated or rewritten as conwell sees fit, as i doubt tg or i will be super motivated to do so or care much about it happening), super stars

a random day: 150

lordstonefish: like clockwork

faminepulse: damej (can be rewritten if needed as i did not contribute enough to the article to have a say in blocking any major updates or improvements)

th4nkyoub3n: 3090, major updates must be approved by dolphinslugchugger or someone dolphinslugchugger trusts to approve such.

the great hippo: the physical world

doctor cimmerian: 2290 by default, as it is now his article.

sorver (discord server): all gaw stuff, all my drafts, permission to finish or use any, finished or otherwise.

prussianblue (irc channel, if no longer around, then referring to any of the regular users of that channel): all my drafts, permission to finish or use any, finished or otherwise.

additionally, though i cannot actively stop anyone from doing so (and indeed i would rather include this here than make a post about it), i would rather be contacted via wikidot (some moderators/administrators + whiteguard are able to get in touch with me offsite) if an article of mine is included or adapted into a paid or commercial project. i will not try to stop any included in commercial projects prior to November 27, 2021, but any after would be nice to be approved by me. all free creations (such as art or cosplay etc.) based off my work is fine, but i do not inherently approve or associate with any. i cannot stop whatever content ends up being made, but i do not endorse anything by default.
[[/collapsible]]
